WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.210 --> 00:00:03.210
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.210 --> 00:00:08.610
&gt;&gt; When I tell people what I do, I'm often
called an idealist.

00:00:08.610 --> 00:00:13.910
People look at me and they say, so, you want
to change the world?

00:00:13.910 --> 00:00:18.840
Well, actually I don't think that we need
to change the world at all.

00:00:18.840 --> 00:00:22.509
I think that the world is perfect as it is.
I think that what we need to change is how

00:00:22.509 --> 00:00:25.829
we treat the world, our
attitudes toward the world.

00:00:25.829 --> 00:00:30.529
&gt;&gt; My name is Lee White and I live here.
When we consider the state of the world, economic

00:00:30.529 --> 00:00:35.210
collapse, climate
change, species depletion, food crises, acts

00:00:35.210 --> 00:00:39.170
of genocide, terrorism and
a war, and the increasing disparities between

00:00:39.170 --> 00:00:42.070
those who have and those
who don't, it's daunting.

00:00:42.070 --> 00:00:44.769
&gt;&gt; We live in the globalized world where corporations
are getting

00:00:44.769 --> 00:00:48.570
more and more influence and have more reach
than governments which are

00:00:48.570 --> 00:00:51.050
in many cases bound to their national borders.

00:00:51.050 --> 00:00:53.890
&gt;&gt; I actually believe now that enough people
can see through the

00:00:53.890 --> 00:00:57.250
illusionary way which banks can and legally
do conjure into existence

00:00:57.250 --> 00:00:59.260
money out of thin air.

00:00:59.260 --> 00:01:01.829
&gt;&gt; There are many puzzles and mysteries in
the mechanisms of aging.

00:01:01.829 --> 00:01:06.140
Equally puzzling is why the fight against
aging is not on the world's

00:01:06.140 --> 00:01:08.740
agenda.
Are just a few people interested in why we're

00:01:08.740 --> 00:01:09.740
aging?

00:01:09.740 --> 00:01:13.090
&gt;&gt; Critics like Danbesa Moyo have accurately
and truthfully pointed out

00:01:13.090 --> 00:01:16.321
that we have sent billions and billions of
our tax dollars to the

00:01:16.321 --> 00:01:18.320
developing world and much it of it has just
disappeared.

00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:21.119
It's also true that when you are just dumping
money from a rich country

00:01:21.119 --> 00:01:24.229
to a poor country that you can create dependence.
These are problems with aid.

00:01:24.229 --> 00:01:27.090
But it's also true as people like Dr. Jeffery
Sacs have accurately

00:01:27.090 --> 00:01:30.549
pointed out targeting specific problems can
create a huge impact that

00:01:30.549 --> 00:01:31.740
help break the cycle of poverty.

00:01:31.740 --> 00:01:36.380
&gt;&gt; I believe in nonviolence struggling, in
fighting against wars in

00:01:36.380 --> 00:01:39.829
this world, in fighting against human rights
violations.

00:01:39.829 --> 00:01:46.500
&gt;&gt; 3 million girls a year are cut forcibly.
FGM happens because women are disempowered.

00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:51.780
They deserve to reach their potential.
They deserve access to education, autonomy

00:01:51.780 --> 00:01:53.840
over their own bodies.

00:01:53.840 --> 00:02:04.600
&gt;&gt; We are portrayed as a world where you have
the North with idea, with

00:02:04.600 --> 00:02:12.671
technology, with capital.
And the South is portrayed as this land of

00:02:12.671 --> 00:02:17.470
lack of opportunity,
corruption, and problems.

00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:23.870
And if that were the case, then the only thing
we need to do is to

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:27.600
transfer money and resources from the North
to the South.

00:02:27.600 --> 00:02:30.860
And we know that is not pathway that we need
to follow.

00:02:30.860 --> 00:02:34.670
&gt;&gt; If we want to survive as a species, folks,
we've got to act together

00:02:34.670 --> 00:02:36.850
as a species.
Thank you for your attention.

00:02:36.850 --> 00:02:37.850
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:37.850 --> 00:02:39.280
NICHOLAS KRISTOF: Well, I'd like to welcome
you here.

00:02:39.280 --> 00:02:43.110
My name is Nicholas Kristof.
I'm a columnist from the New York Times.

00:02:43.110 --> 00:02:47.340
And I -- this is an unusual session in a couple
of ways, but first of

00:02:47.340 --> 00:02:50.920
all, I want to kind of give a bit of a PG
warning.

00:02:50.920 --> 00:02:57.150
And the reason is that we realized as we walked
in, that the topic it

00:02:57.150 --> 00:03:01.160
says "Design Your Cause."
And so I think some of you may be here to

00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:05.590
figure out how to design your
own cause or promote it.

00:03:05.590 --> 00:03:12.950
And this emerged because Julia Lalla-Maharajh
