00:03:12.950 --> 00:03:19.440
happened to be female genital mutilation.
So as a result, this panel is about a discussion

00:03:19.440 --> 00:03:22.861
of where we go and how
we deal with female genital mutilation.

00:03:22.861 --> 00:03:26.510
And we didn't want to have a lot of people
wincing in the audience if

00:03:26.510 --> 00:03:30.270
you were expecting a discussion about, you
know, how one goes about how

00:03:30.270 --> 00:03:32.230
designing your cause.
So fair warning.

00:03:32.230 --> 00:03:41.730
And, of course, this is unusual in that respect
that, you know, we

00:03:41.730 --> 00:03:45.430
associate Davos with turgid discussions of
interest rates and Middle

00:03:45.430 --> 00:03:51.310
East policy and whatever, not particularly
about genital cutting.

00:03:51.310 --> 00:03:55.050
The other way in which this was most unusual
was that this topic arose

00:03:55.050 --> 00:03:58.940
from a YouTube audience.
And we've talked all the time about the importance

00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:01.800
of social media, how
we can build campaigns.

00:04:01.800 --> 00:04:08.240
Well this is an embodiment of precisely that.
And if you are here in the room, of course,

00:04:08.240 --> 00:04:09.700
please turn off your cell
phones.

00:04:09.700 --> 00:04:13.251
If you are at home watching on YouTube, then
turn on your cell phones

00:04:13.251 --> 00:04:24.250
really loudly and just hit pause.
Um, as I said, this topic arose because people

00:04:24.250 --> 00:04:28.969
on YouTube were invited
to vote among some competing ideas, some competing

00:04:28.969 --> 00:04:32.770
causes.
And Julia Lalla-Maharajh, I want to -- you

00:04:32.770 --> 00:04:35.419
want to raise your hand
there?

00:04:35.419 --> 00:04:43.099
Um, Julia submitted a video which explains
her passion, her cause, and

00:04:43.099 --> 00:04:44.640
let's cut to that now.

00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:46.420
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:46.420 --> 00:04:52.150
JULIA LALLA-MAHARAJH: Last year, I volunteered
in Ethiopia.

00:04:52.150 --> 00:04:57.120
