00:49:07.470 --> 00:49:10.650
human rights education in
San Francisco, so I wrote a paper last year

00:49:10.650 --> 00:49:14.240
on FGM.
In the literature, I noticed that one of the

00:49:14.240 --> 00:49:17.230
reasons why the women are
continuing the cutting is because it's one

00:49:17.230 --> 00:49:19.029
of -- it's their means of
economic sustainability.

00:49:19.029 --> 00:49:22.289
So I was wondering given that it's the Economic
Forum, what

00:49:22.289 --> 00:49:25.920
public/private sector partnerships have been
built-in, if there are any

00:49:25.920 --> 00:49:29.059
subsidies that governments might be giving
to women to help them

00:49:29.059 --> 00:49:33.380
transition from this profession, and what
means are -- what else we can

00:49:33.380 --> 00:49:36.329
do as civil society actors to help move that
