to the extent that those
people speak the language and have local credibility

01:05:26.460 --> 01:05:27.460
and authority.

01:05:27.460 --> 01:05:29.099
&gt;&gt; Sorry.
Very, very quickly but I mean, the communities

01:05:29.099 --> 01:05:32.089
that did used to
practice it, that's what I mean.

01:05:32.089 --> 01:05:35.900
Like you mentioned in Senegal or Mauritania
where there's a community

01:05:35.900 --> 01:05:40.200
that it was recently actually practiced and
then given up because I

01:05:40.200 --> 01:05:42.630
think that's the most credible voice.

01:05:42.630 --> 01:05:48.770
NICHOLAS KRISTOF: Very good point.
I want to now kind of wind up and for those

01:05:48.770 --> 01:05:52.539
who didn't get a chance to
ask your questions, you know, feel free to

01:05:52.539 --> 01:05:53.980
mob the folks here
afterward.

01:05:53.980 --> 01:06:01.660
But we've been talking about something that
happens to 3 million girls

01:06:01.660 --> 01:06:04.440
a year.
Human rights violation, I think we agree on

01:06:04.440 --> 01:06:09.510
a vast scale.
Leads to more maternal mortality, leads to

01:06:09.510 --> 01:06:13.650
more girls dying of
infection at a scale, and we don't really

01:06:13.650 --> 01:06:16.490
know.
When a girl dies after she's been cut, people

01:06:16.490 --> 01:06:18.910
just say, oh she just
died of malaria.

01:06:18.910 --> 01:06:22.849
People don't acknowledge how often this happens.
But what do we do?

01:06:22.849 --> 01:06:28.069
Somebody is here wants to get involved; somebody
is watching on

01:06:28.069 --> 01:06:31.599
YouTube.
They can go to the Tostan website which is

01:06:31.599 --> 01:06:36.309
Tostan.org T-O-S-T-A-N.org,
learn more about it in that way.

01:06:36.309 --> 01:06:45.009
They can go to Julia's website.
And I'll -- I'll -- I don't know.

01:06:45.009 --> 01:06:46.009
I'm sure --

01:06:46.009 --> 01:06:51.470
JULIA LALLA-MAHARAJH: Which is EndFGMnow.org
But also another excellent website is ForwardUK.org.uk,

01:06:51.470 --> 01:06:54.529
which is where
I volunteer as well.

01:06:54.529 --> 01:06:58.250
NICHOLAS KRISTOF: Let me -- so let's go systematically
through here

01:06:58.250 --> 01:07:00.980
and maybe Kathy you can start.
You know, what does somebody do?

01:07:00.980 --> 01:07:06.210
KATHY CALVIN: Well, I think it's awesome that
this -- that the YouTube

01:07:06.210 --> 01:07:09.080
community chose this issue and already has
stood up for it.

01:07:09.080 --> 01:07:12.970
So having a voice is the first thing.
The second is to become an advocate for girls.

01:07:12.970 --> 01:07:17.249
If you haven't seen the girl effect video
which is on YouTube, it's an

01:07:17.249 --> 01:07:20.641
awesome thing and I think it gives you sense
of the positive that if

01:07:20.641 --> 01:07:23.940
you can be become an advocate for girls we
can end should have these

01:07:23.940 --> 01:07:27.019
trouble some things.
I think you had a great idea which is instead

01:07:27.019 --> 01:07:31.020
of shame and blame, we
ought to be finding those who've already begun

01:07:31.020 --> 01:07:33.859
to fight back and, you
know, we all probably need to do a better

01:07:33.859 --> 01:07:37.980
job of thanking Uganda for
just making the thing against the law right

01:07:37.980 --> 01:07:40.749
now.
So I think we all have voices and we should

01:07:40.749 --> 01:07:43.190
be using them more and
we've got the tools now.

01:07:43.190 --> 01:07:47.470
LARRY COX: Well, first of all, I think it's
clear to everybody that

01:07:47.470 --> 01:07:52.080
this is part of a larger struggle for women's
rights in general and I

01:07:52.080 --> 01:07:56.779
think.
And I'm happy to be agreeing with Nick on

01:07:56.779 --> 01:07:59.099
this that this is a
particular moment in history where this battle

01:07:59.099 --> 01:08:03.770
really is ripe, can
really be -- there can be a sea change in

01:08:03.770 --> 01:08:06.609
the world.
I think FGM is part of that issue.

01:08:06.609 --> 01:08:10.170
I don't think it's the only one, but it's
a continuum of how we raise

01:08:10.170 --> 01:08:13.779
the status of women and how we just make intolerable
practices that

01:08:13.779 --> 01:08:17.759
have seemed tolerable.
And there's myriad ways for people to get

01:08:17.759 --> 01:08:21.920
involved and it's not only a
question of the west against the developing

01:08:21.920 --> 01:08:26.150
world that it's also a
question of the fight within each country

01:08:26.150 --> 01:08:28.140
where these issues are still
involved.

01:08:28.140 --> 01:08:31.460
So I think that's the first thing and the
second thing is that Amnesty

01:08:31.460 --> 01:08:36.250
is involved right now in a campaign in Europe
to, to try to change the

01:08:36.250 --> 01:08:39.650
practices and policies of the European Union
to make sure that they are

01:08:39.650 --> 01:08:41.670
supporting the kind of approaches that we've
talked about here.

01:08:41.670 --> 01:08:43.580
It's very easy for people to get involved
in that.

01:08:43.580 --> 01:08:47.710
They can Google their local Amnesty website
for whatever country

01:08:47.710 --> 01:08:51.460
they're in.
And also to make sure that women who are trying

01:08:51.460 --> 01:08:56.819
to get refuge in this
country or in countries in Europe because

01:08:56.819 --> 01:09:02.839
they have a legitimate fear
of being forced to be cut, that the laws are

01:09:02.839 --> 01:09:05.119
changed to make that
possible for them to do.

01:09:05.119 --> 01:09:08.400
NICHOLAS KRISTOF: And Julia, in case anybody
doesn't have your website

01:09:08.400 --> 01:09:09.400
down yet --

01:09:09.400 --> 01:09:14.920
JULIA LALLA-MAHARAJH: Clearly, the website
but what I really think we

01:09:14.920 --> 01:09:21.909
need to do is make FGM much more explicit.
The data, the porosity of the data is shocking.

01:09:21.909 --> 01:09:28.719
There is a lot that's out there.
But how can we ascertain the global scale

01:09:28.719 --> 01:09:32.509
of this issue if we don't
actually know what we're dealing with?

01:09:32.509 --> 01:09:35.869
The 3 million figure we're all quoting is
in Africa alone?

01:09:35.869 --> 01:09:43.679
It doesn't tackle Indonesia, Yemen, UAE.
It doesn't tackle Europe, where we know 500,000

01:09:43.679 --> 01:09:45.790
women are living with
FGM.

01:09:45.790 --> 01:09:50.060
So we don't understand the scale.
We don't understand what needs to be done

01:09:50.060 --> 01:09:53.710
on a country-by-country basis
to tackle the problem.

01:09:53.710 --> 01:09:57.710
A solution in Indonesia is completely different
to what we need in

01:09:57.710 --> 01:10:01.760
Cameroon, in Sierra Leone, as Ann has said,
in Senegal.

01:10:01.760 --> 01:10:06.260
We need to be very, very cognizant of what
is the global action plan?

01:10:06.260 --> 01:10:13.190
Without that, we can't cost a solution.
If this is a matter of resources, then great.

01:10:13.190 --> 01:10:18.850
Let's just get on and fundraise.
But until we are much more aware about the

01:10:18.850 --> 01:10:22.889
global scale of this problem
and what needs to be done about it, we can't

01:10:22.889 --> 01:10:28.500
reach that target of 2015.
I think very kind offer from an NGO already

01:10:28.500 --> 01:10:32.639
working in this field --
thank you, I'll be in touch -- but equally,

01:10:32.639 --> 01:10:37.429
all the NGOs working in
this area, please get FGM on your agenda.

01:10:37.429 --> 01:10:42.560
Do something more about it.
And I've run out of steam.

01:10:42.560 --> 01:10:46.420
Go to my website.
There are five easy things that you can do.

01:10:46.420 --> 01:10:50.810
They may seem little things.
But lastly, do what you can.

01:10:50.810 --> 01:10:55.590
This is going out to the YouTube community.
They'll be people watching all over the world.

01:10:55.590 --> 01:11:00.060
I chose to enter a competition on Davos; you
may want to find out what

01:11:00.060 --> 01:11:03.600
is happening in your local community.
You may wish to fundraise.

01:11:03.600 --> 01:11:08.130
You may wish to push your government on various
things or your MP.

01:11:08.130 --> 01:11:11.070
Know what your action is and what your agency
is.

01:11:11.070 --> 01:11:16.199
And please just do something.
It's international FGM day, sorry.

01:11:16.199 --> 01:11:19.869
International anti-FGM day on the sixth of
February.

01:11:19.869 --> 01:11:23.420
That's a week today.
Contact a journalist.

01:11:23.420 --> 01:11:25.910
Talk about FGM. Thank you.

01:11:25.910 --> 01:11:29.600
NICHOLAS KRISTOF: Don't feel you have to contact
this journalist in

01:11:29.600 --> 01:11:33.900
particular.
I'm already on board.

01:11:33.900 --> 01:11:34.900
Ann?

01:11:34.900 --> 01:11:38.600
ANN VENEMAN: Well, certainly I would agree
with all that's been said.

01:11:38.600 --> 01:11:44.210
But I think it's -- first of all, so important
to recognize that this

01:11:44.210 --> 01:11:49.300
is first and foremost a violation of the rights
of the girl child.

01:11:49.300 --> 01:11:53.940
Think about the fact that most of the people,
the children who are

01:11:53.940 --> 01:12:01.150
subjected to this are between about the ages
of 4 and maybe 12.

01:12:01.150 --> 01:12:08.460
I mean, this is a human being that really
doesn't have the right to say

01:12:08.460 --> 01:12:12.030
no.
It's imposed on her.

01:12:12.030 --> 01:12:15.920
The second thing I would say is that everyone
should look at those

01:12:15.920 --> 01:12:20.929
organizations that are working in this arena.
It isn't a popular cause.

01:12:20.929 --> 01:12:26.550
These organizations can't generate lots of
resources for their work.

01:12:26.550 --> 01:12:30.150
And so support those organizations that are
truly making a difference

01:12:30.150 --> 01:12:31.700
in this area.

01:12:31.700 --> 01:12:37.260
NICHOLAS KRISTOF: Um, let me just also say,
finally, that, you know,

01:12:37.260 --> 01:12:43.260
this is indeed just part of a broader puzzle.
And that quite aside from the simple moral

01:12:43.260 --> 01:12:47.179
issue, it's imminently
practical issue we're not going to make progress

01:12:47.179 --> 01:12:52.639
against global
poverty, against insecurity unless girls are

01:12:52.639 --> 01:12:56.000
brought into the picture
brought into the formal economy, educated,

01:12:56.000 --> 01:12:58.800
and so on.
This is one facet of that larger picture.

01:12:58.800 --> 01:13:03.520
And then we really hope that you whether you're
here, right here, or

01:13:03.520 --> 01:13:10.199
watching on YouTube, you will get engaged.
And I think Julia really deserves our thanks

01:13:10.199 --> 01:13:15.760
and appreciation for
bringing this issue to Davos and to YouTube

01:13:15.760 --> 01:13:19.139
to the Davos debate.
And please join me in thanking her and all

01:13:19.139 --> 01:13:29.410
of the panelists here today.

